
# Dockerized Symfony App

Clone the project

```bash
  git clone https://github.com/Faez-B/symfony-easy-admin.git
```

Go to the project directory

```bash
  cd symfony-easy-admin
```
## Run Locally

```bash
  cd app
```
### Composer installation

```bash
  composer install
```

### NPM installation

```bash
  npm install
```

### Start the server

```bash
  symfony serve
```

### Run the NPM script
  
  ```bash
    npm run watch
  ```

Go to ```127.0.0.1:8000```

## Or you can run with Docker
Launch the containers

```bash
docker compose up --build -d
```

Go to ```127.0.0.1```

### Available routes
  
  ```bash
    /         : ROLE_USER
    /admin    : ROLE_ADMIN
    /login    : PUBLIC_ACCESS
    /register : PUBLIC_ACCESS
  ```
